{
  "stem": "20083.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had no-- nothing to say in that matter, absolutely nothing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have nothing to say in that matter, either.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, No, not in any way either disassociate or any other way.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We just lived the way you and I talk, and religion did not enter our lives.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's very easy because the Nuremberg Laws of 1935, first of all, deprived my father of all his Christian clientele, his patients could no longer visit him, only Jewish patients.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So from a professional point-of-view, it was very, very rough on him and he suffered tremendously.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course he was no longer permitted even to visit sick patients who were not Jewish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And apparently, it had such-- it had such an effect on him that he had a stroke in about 1937, shortly after the Olympic games in Berlin of 1936.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As far as my mother was concerned, she could still have her-- oddly enough-- still have her Christian or Aryan renters, the ones who lodged with her.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And these people knew about us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And except for one incident, we never had any problem with them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In fact, there was one man, his name was Winkelman, who happened to be a hunchbacked little artist.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he was responsible mostly for sketching and drawing swastikas, swastika emblems, for the various Nazi parties in Germany.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he was violently anti-Nazi, but that's how he made his-- his living.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "On the-- next to him lived a Fraulein Mueller, a Miss Mueller, who was very anti-- who was very pro-Nazi.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one day when I was sick, I was visited by three members of the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Of course, I was sick in bed with the flu.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I remember that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was-- that was about 1936 or 1937.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
